quran[12]{c,v,t}:
  35,19,Not alike are the blind and the seeing
  35,20,Nor are (depths of) darkness and light
  35,21,Nor are the shade and the sun's heat
  35,22,"Nor are the living and the dead. Verily, Allah makes whom He wills to hear, but you cannot make hear those who are in graves"
  35,23,You are only a warner
  35,24,"Verily, We have sent you with the truth, a bearer of glad tidings and a warner. And there never was a nation but a warner had passed among them"
  35,25,"And if they deny you, those before them also denied. Their Messengers came to them with clear signs, and with the Scriptures, and with the Book giving light"
  35,26,"Then I took hold of those who disbelieved, and how terrible was My denial"
  35,27,"See you not that Allah sends down water from the sky, and We produce therewith fruits of various colors, and among the mountains are Judad, white and red, of varying colors and (others) Gharabib black"
  35,28,"And likewise, men and moving creature and cattle are of various colors. It is only those among His servants who have knowledge that fear Allah. Verily, Allah is Almighty, Oft-Forgiving"
  35,29,"Verily, those who recite the Book of Allah, and perform the Salah, and spend out of what We have provided for them, secretly and openly, they hope for a (sure) trade-gain that will never perish"
  35,30,"That He may pay them their wages in full, and give them (even) more, out of His grace. Verily, He is Oft-Forgiving, Most Ready to appreciate"